def conv(value):
    if value == 1:
        return "yes"
    else:
        return "No"

df['SeniorCitizen'] = df["SeniorCitizen"].apply(conv)

Visualization¶

In [25]:
ax = sns.countplot(x = 'Churn'  , data = df)
ax.bar_label(ax.containers[0])
plt.title('Count of Customers by churn')
plt.show()
In [24]:
plt.figure(figsize = (4,4))
grb = df.groupby("Churn").agg({'Churn':"count"})
plt.pie(grb['Churn'], labels = grb.index , autopct = "%1.2f%%")
plt.title("Percentage of churned Customers" , fontsize = 10)
plt.show()

26.54 percent of people have churned Out services

In [62]:
numeric_features = ['MonthlyCharges', 'TotalCharges', 'tenure']

plt.figure(figsize=(15, 5))
for i, feature in enumerate(numeric_features, 1):
    plt.subplot(1, 3, i)
    sns.boxplot(data=df, x='Churn', y=feature, palette='Set2')
    plt.title(f'{feature} vs Churn')
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

In [85]:
import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# Select relevant numerical columns for the pairplot
pairplot_columns = ['tenure', 'MonthlyCharges', 'TotalCharges']

# Create the pairplot with increased figure size
# The height parameter specifies the height of each subplot
sns.pairplot(df, vars=pairplot_columns, hue='Churn', palette='coolwarm', height=3)

# Show the plot
plt.suptitle('Pairplot of Selected Variables', y=1.02)  # Add title
plt.show()
